reviews.text: Awesome place for a great sunrise walk or even a sundown walk. My family and I have even went at 1 a.m. and it was still great. Well lit and always feel safe there.
Very peaceful place to spend time with family, alone, or get a nice walk/jog. There are plenty of spots to take nice picture's because of the scenery. One of my favorite locations.

Beautiful view and well maintained walk. Great place to go walking, mornings, evenings or anytime. Open to bicycle use also. The breeze is usually pretty nice and it's a good place to view fireworks on the holidays that have them. Parking can be a little hard to find.
Very nice, quiet walk on the river. The path under the Main St Bridge is very cool. It drops down near level with the waterline and gives a great view of the north bank.

Ok, so its unlikely to be on a typical European holiday makers 'must see' list - but if you're in the area - and the Jax beaches, A1A drive, Amelia Island and St. Augustine area is great for scenery, nature trails, cycling, fishing and even (rare in the US) historical sites - then the Jacksonville river-walk is worth a try. They've obviously spent a lot of money rejuvenating the north & south riverbanks and they look great though there's some hurricane damage still to fix. We were even lucky enough to see dolphins hunting between the bridges. The Saturday artist market and ample free parking make it the best day to visit.

One of the best and cheapest breakfast places in Indy.  The Donut Shop is a local business that has been around for decades, and it hasn't changed much that entire time.  The donuts are delicious and they have plenty of breakfast and lunch options.  The food is always good and inexpensive.  Service is always consistent.  This place has been a staple my whole life.
Their donuts are the besttttt! It really shows a symbol that they are doing their best to make their donuts flavorful and beautiful too. It’s appreciated and I recommend you visit this Donut shop
We had the chocolate and the honey glazed. Both were so soft and delicious. Will definitely return
Great diner type experience. Good old fashioned breakfast. Great prices. Just remember to bring cash. They don't except cards.
If on donuts alone, it'd be 5 stars. But the food is OK and the coffee was a little worse. Still, cheap food and quick service.

No place around does the volume of meals as China Garden. It's a constant stop for Chinese tour buses on the weekend. Their dim sum is solid, but it's convenient if you're in DC or Arlington to get here compared to Falls Church or Silver Spring. The lady that runs the place can be a tad truculent, but she gives the place atmosphere.

Always feel free to reach out to me on Twitter @joerazz
Good Dim Sum food cart. It can get very busy during weekends due to tourist buses.  Excellent quality for Chinese party food. Unfortunately, they closed down in July 2017 and moved to Maryland.

Dim sum on a Saturday noon was surprisingly not busy.  The dumplings we're good, not great.  The roast duck was amazing, huge, fatty and full of flavor.  The ginger scallion lobster was also ok.  Service was very attentive.  Validated parking in the basement.

I used to be a motorcoach operator and brought many Asian Tour groups to this restaurant.
The food was always delicious. I was last at this restaurant in 2008.
If Asians eat at an Asian food establishment, the food has to be good. The food tastes just like quality restaurants in Chinatown, NYC

Pretty mediocre, but that might have been my bad for showing up right at the end of dim sum service. I got served cold squid, which luckily they replaced, and dumplings that had the stale texture of having been sitting out for hours. Would have been better if they had just told me no more dim sum.

What a fun place to go with a family that is really hungry and ready for some entertainment. This dining experience was entertaining from the start. Immediately as you get to the restaurant outside you have beautiful Japanese garden with some gorgeous prize-winning goldfishes. They kids had so much fun looking at them swimming and everything.  After all of that excitement we were able to be seated at a Japanese Hibachi Table with another family and kids so my children had a lot of fun interacting with everyone else around the table. As the chef came in he quickly started his show and it was fun interactive and very energetic. There was so much food!!!! Your portions are very large so make sure you come hungry. the typical Hibachi chicken dinner included rice vegetables and before that you get to have soup and salad. The only reason I took a star of was that the food was not as flavorful or authentic as I am used to but for being Japanese attraction chain spot it was sort of expected to be a little Bland however it was perfect for kiddos taste buds.

The food is surprisingly better than one might think. The salad that comes out with the soup prior to the meal is delicious I really like the dressing here. I did not care for the sushi as it did not seem as fresh as some places. The steak and chicken combo I ordered was well-cooked and affordable.

We arrived around 5:30, no one else in the dining area except for a group that was finishing up. We waited 15-20min before getting our drinks. A party of 16 arrived after we got our drinks. We had already ordered when another group joined our table. We still had not received our salads or soup an HOUR after being seated, but the party’s food was being cooked and served. Poor management. We were told that the party arrived before us, when they actually MOVED us from the table the party was sitting at to serve us quicker. The manager that I spoke with said “they knew what they wanted to eat, they had a list” I DON’T CARE if they had a list, we had ordered our food BEFORE the party placed their order. Waiting an hour and not receiving soups and salads is unacceptable in my book.

This place has always been pretty good. However the service has really gone down hill. No refills for the entire meal. Wrong food served. Appetizers brought after meal. Very small portions. Time to search for new place to eat.

Yes yes!! Best sushi presentation in Tennessee. Chef Boy knows how to make a birthday special. I told him to surprise me and yes I was surprised with a great sushi dinner.. will always be my go to place for sushi!!

Great place with vintage diner decor and atmosphere. They know how to cook eggs and serve amazing diner coffee (even decaf). Can be a bit pricey, but it's a definite treat and one spot I hit any time I'm in Burlington.

I got corned beef hash with two eggs. Eggs cooked exactly as requested, corned beef was tender but not mush, homefries crispy but not dry. Staff was polite and attentive. Great value for some excellent diner food! Was *very* busy at 1pm on a Saturday.
The food's good. The Waitresses are nice. Portions are very good. A little on the pricey side for a diner. But I'd go there again!

This review is long overdue. I have been to Henry's for a few times and Henry's never disappoints me. It remains my first choice for breakfast because of friendly and more importantly efficient staff, wonderful homemade food particularly corned beef hash, and the old diner atmosphere. I even brought my wife's family there when they visited us from Hong Kong. Sometimes you need to wait because Henry's popular. I recommend going there before 8:15am Sunday morning to beat the crowd.
I had my first meal (lunch) at Henry's Diner. It was great in taste and all of my friends loved it. Good value for money. Appreciate their chocolate and strawberry pies.

Just like the one at home. They have huge screens and are a good size for large parties. They can accommodate a large group. Please call in advance for large parties. Good selection at the bar, all your favorite drinks and some local brew. I went back the next day and was treated just as good. I liked the service and the staff was really trying to get me everything I asked for.

The food is set by the company, and the back end fulfills their end of the deal by making great, casual food. However, the front end customer service leaves something to be desired. Too long to come back to table. Little menu knowledge (this has been on three occasions in the past month). If you want to watch the game and dont care about customer service, then 5 stars.
The patron was very attentive and very helpful. The appetizers were delicious and the pulled pork sandwich could have used less salt but overall good. There were no images due to the gobbled up food.
The food was good but what made the experience even better was our server!! She was amazing... just wished I could remember her name.  I would hire her in a heartbeat

Atmosphere is their main attraction. The wings are ok. Let's face it you go for the drinks and sports.  However the burger never disappoints.  Bloody Mary could use some tweaking.  I've had better. Can't mess up the draft drinks. Service is slow so order a drink before you get to the glass half-empty.
